	]
	quest.1DCBC94F0A8D171E.title: "&6Hoenn League"
	quest.1E4CAAC510D62A5F.quest_desc: ["The &eFilter&r allows items to enter an inventory only if that item type already exists inside."]
	quest.1EA2B20232E269BF.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 15"
	quest.1EA2B20232E269BF.title: "Hugh"
	quest.1ECE67F6DA1294FC.quest_desc: [
		"The Inventory Linker is a powerful block who can be link with your inventory using a Player Paper."
		""
		"It needs rotational force underneath to work, you can output from it and input inside using Funnel (for example)."
		""
		"You have 3 different configuration on top."
		"Inventory, Armor and Off Hand."
		""
		"Each configuration is link to you, so you can, for example, extract cobblestone from your inventory using a funnel with a filter."
		"Or you can equip an armor automatically, injecting an armor into it."
	]
	quest.1F0411235971D6F7.quest_desc: ["Hoenn is renowned for its diverse and contrasting wildlife. Some Pokémon favor marshes, others inhabit mountainsides or deep caves. Capture 40 specimens and you’ll start to grasp this richness. Stay alert—many Hoenn Pokémon are shaped by extreme environments."]
	quest.1F0411235971D6F7.title: "Obtain 40 different Pokémon from Generation 3's Pokédex"
	quest.1F3AF58B2297B52E.quest_desc: ["&fCandice, the Ice-type Gym Leader of Snowpoint City, is one of the official Sinnoh Gym World Tour battles. Defeat this leader, claim the matching badge, and continue your regional progression."]
	quest.1F3AF58B2297B52E.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 77"
	quest.1F3AF58B2297B52E.title: "Candice"
	quest.20153E139D596C8C.quest_desc: ["Acts as an interface similar to those found in &bAE2&r systems."]
	quest.20976935DD7F2CC2.quest_subtitle: "Restore the ancestor of all birds!"
	quest.20976935DD7F2CC2.title: "The Wings of Prehistory"
	quest.209941E5B135982B.quest_desc: ["You’ve explored everything Sinnoh has to offer—its rigor, mysticism, and deep roots. Thanks to you, knowledge is reborn. You now carry the echo of this region within you."]
	quest.209941E5B135982B.title: "Obtain all 107 different Pokémon from Generation 4's Pokédex"
	quest.20A9045213580DAA.title: "Falkner"
	quest.20E56946F53C2005.quest_desc: [
		"At the bottom of the inventory, you may have noticed a search bar."
		""
		"This is the &dJust Enough Items&r, or &dJEI&r, search bar. "
		""
		"If you type \"Wood\", for example, the &dJEI &ritem list at the right of the screen will show all items with \"Wood\" in the name."
		""
		"Adding a @ at the start of the search query will show the items from a specific mod, for example @Chipped"
	]
	quest.20E56946F53C2005.quest_subtitle: "Read my description!"
	quest.20EC86E8567AA38A.quest_desc: ["Collect a bucket of Biodiesel."]
	quest.210E5426B9F23747.quest_desc: ["So you have a chest wall that you want to connect to your storage/crafting interface? Well the Inventory Connecter is for you! Put the connecter in the middle of your chests, and make sure all the chests are touching. Chests adjacent to the connecter extend the connecters range, so you can have as many chests to a connecter as you want"]
	quest.210E5426B9F23747.quest_subtitle: "Storage Wall"
	quest.216212CDA2B4AC1B.quest_subtitle: "Sides of the &cBrass Tunnel&r can be &aFiltered&r to only allow certain items to pass. If multiple outputs are available, items will be treated according to the tunnel's setting, being split by default."
	quest.216212CDA2B4AC1B.title: "Craft &6Brass Funnels"
	quest.21979702BF28B521.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 85"
	quest.21979702BF28B521.title: "Archie"
	quest.2231B9FF6BB3CEB7.quest_subtitle: "If you want to make a &9quarry&r or &9tunnel bore&r, then you'll be needing a few of these. Attach them to a moving contraption and they will mine any block they run into."
	quest.2231B9FF6BB3CEB7.title: "Craft &5Mechanical Drill"
	quest.224A14C412DE7B50.quest_desc: ["The Waystone is a powerful tool for quick travel across the world. By activating Waystones, you can teleport between them for faster exploration and travel.\\n\\nTo use a Waystone:\\n1. Find or craft a Waystone (you’ll need a few resources).\\n2. Right-click on the Waystone to activate it.\\n3. Once activated, you can teleport to it from any other Waystone you’ve unlocked.\\n4. To teleport, simply open the Waystone menu and select your destination.\\n\\nNote: You can only teleport to Waystones that you have previously activated. Enjoy your fast travels!"]
	quest.224A14C412DE7B50.quest_subtitle: "&eWaystone Explanation"
	quest.225465778A21D04B.quest_desc: ["A Mechanical Belt is a mechanical component that conveys rotation and moves items and entities. Placing a Belt requires at least two Shafts and can be 20 blocks long"]
	quest.225465778A21D04B.title: "Craft &bMechanical Belts"
	quest.2259C8B3F283D4FD.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 75"
	quest.2259C8B3F283D4FD.title: "Micah"
	quest.2269ABF6B576AF24.quest_desc: [
		"&fArtazon's artistic Grass-type Gym Leader turns battle into a living masterpiece."
		"&fDefeat Brassius to claim the Grass Badge."
	]
	quest.2269ABF6B576AF24.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 100"
	quest.2269ABF6B576AF24.title: "Brassius"
	quest.2291E0D4BD84B464.quest_subtitle: "&bJungle, Magical, Mountain, Sky, Volcanic"
	quest.22FE3BB6CCC777BE.quest_subtitle: "&bJungle, Swamp"
	quest.230C80ADED89931C.title: "Craft &6Copper Wire"
	quest.233298CE83D842DF.quest_desc: ["Vaults are used for automatic storage and retrieval of large amounts of items. They cannot be manually accessed however. Automate!"]
	quest.233298CE83D842DF.title: "Craft &bItem Vault"
	quest.23AF41B039B8C705.quest_desc: ["Bruno believes strength comes from body and mind. He trains daily with his Fighting-types — and is said to punch through solid rock with his bare hands."]
	quest.23AF41B039B8C705.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 85"
	quest.23AF41B039B8C705.title: "Bruno"
	quest.23EF98480984F6DE.quest_subtitle: "&9Disenchant items&r and collect experience as liquid. If a player stands on it xp will also be extracted."
	quest.23EF98480984F6DE.title: "Craft &6Disenchanter"
