	quest.268351B03079CCBB.title: "&6Sinnoh Trainer Progression"
	quest.26945829BD98682E.title: "If you need switch to the Modpack serie"
	quest.269A3318AFDED628.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 31"
	quest.26B6F237AF32AC4E.title: "Defeat pokemon from each type"
	quest.26BB6886D34DAAAC.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.26BB6886D34DAAAC.quest_subtitle: "&2Used to make a Blaze Enchanter seethe and applies an enchant 1 level above the set enchantment applied.&r"
	quest.26C4E9AE00308502.quest_subtitle: "Capture one Pokémon of each classic type: Grass, Fire, and Water"
	quest.26C4E9AE00308502.title: "The Elemental Triad"
	quest.26CC5A82C2F3365D.title: "Capture the legendary &aBulu"
	quest.2714A2EC7A917167.quest_desc: [
		"Right now your mechanical arm you'll use it in the craft of the Nasa Workbench, but this one can be useful in automation of Create devices!"
		""
		"The Mechanical Arm is a block used to transfer items."
		"The Mechanical Arm can take or deposit items from various blocks within a 5 block radius of where it is placed. The order it does this in is determined by its behavior as well as the order the blocks were selected in during placement. A placed Mechanical Arm's selected blocks can be viewed by hovering over it with a Wrench. "
	]
	quest.2729C781A3E7D2AF.quest_desc: [
		"&9📦 Introducing the Luggage Companion!&r  "
		"&fTired of losing dropped items while mining or exploring? Meet the Luggage—your personal walking chest! Just craft it, place it, and it will follow you around, automatically collecting any nearby items you drop. Right-click to open its inventory, or Shift+right-click to pick it up—including all contents.  "
		""
		"&f⚡ Lightning upgrade! If struck by lightning or placed in Witch Water, it becomes “charged”—doubling its storage from single to double chest capacity.  "
		""
		"&6🔋 Durable and convenient—perfect for adventuring with full hands!  "
		"&fGet ready to level up your storage game with Luggage!"
	]
	quest.273A2D047C98D58F.quest_desc: [
		"&fBlackthorn City's Dragon-type Gym Leader is proud, demanding, and fiercely powerful."
		"&fDefeat Clair to claim the Rising Badge."
	]
	quest.273A2D047C98D58F.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 45"
	quest.273A2D047C98D58F.title: "Clair"
	quest.2740232C6B1B018E.title: "&fA Wild &dZacian &fAppeared!"
	quest.2748A6302CE3ACC6.quest_desc: ["Tesla Coil use Forge Energy to charge item"]
	quest.2789661B22C98366.quest_subtitle: "A true master of prehistoric Pokémon!"
	quest.2789661B22C98366.title: "Fossil Mastery"
	quest.27B3F4E4C6C34510.title: "Capture the legendary &cVolcanion"
	quest.27CB2821D0EA92C5.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.27CB2821D0EA92C5.quest_subtitle: "Andesite Alloy is a material used in Andesite Casing and simple kinetic blocks, which serves as an entry-point to the mechanical components of Create"
	quest.27E206948965351D.quest_desc: [
		""
		""
		"Create is a mod offering a variety of tools and blocks for Building, Decoration and Aesthetic Automation."
		""
		"The added elements of tech are designed to leave as many design choices to the player as possible. With Create, the game isn't played inside a bunch of UIs, it challenges you to setup contraptions of animated components working together in many possible arrangements."
	]
	quest.27E206948965351D.quest_subtitle: "&6&lWelcome To Create!"
	quest.27E68E31EC21675B.quest_subtitle: "&aGantry Carriages&r move along &aGantry Shafts&r and will move any blocks or super glued structures attached to it at the same time."
	quest.27EAABF8E021A364.quest_desc: ["&fBurgh, the Bug-type Gym Leader of Castelia City, is one of the official Unova Gym World Tour battles. Defeat this leader, claim the matching badge, and continue your regional progression."]
	quest.27EAABF8E021A364.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 84"
	quest.27EAABF8E021A364.title: "Burgh"
	quest.280BC148D9DAD250.quest_desc: ["You’ve cataloged all the Pokémon from Paldea. Their diversity, their strangeness, their vitality... All of this makes this region a key milestone in your encyclopedia. You’ve just opened a window to the future."]
	quest.280BC148D9DAD250.title: "Obtain 120 different Pokémon from Generation 9's Pokédex"
	quest.28894A6E8BD319CD.quest_subtitle: "Can be used to drain or fill any large area of liquid. If used on a large enough pool of Lava it will count it as an infinite source of Lava. Handy!"
	quest.28894A6E8BD319CD.title: "Craft &6Hose Pulley"
	quest.289010CE545DB1E6.quest_desc: ["Used to paint and customize framed cables and blocks."]
	quest.28A1FE67951514B7.quest_desc: ["You can get Brass Ingot using the Mixer."]
	quest.28A1FE67951514B7.quest_subtitle: "The age of Brass"
	quest.28EDBA72C5D4F4FE.quest_desc: [
		"&fMontenevera's Ghost-type Gym Leader mixes rhythm, spirits, and pressure."
		"&fDefeat Ryme to claim the Ghost Badge."
	]
	quest.28EDBA72C5D4F4FE.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 100"
	quest.28EDBA72C5D4F4FE.title: "Ryme"
	quest.28F2C99C138FAC6F.quest_desc: ["The islands of Alola are protected by powerful Pokémon, the Island Guardians. But even without encountering these divine beings, you’ll feel their influence in the local fauna. At 70 captures, you’ll become a true expert of Alola’s legends, while observing the behaviors of rare and impressive species."]
	quest.28F2C99C138FAC6F.title: "Obtain 70 different Pokémon from Generation 7's Pokédex"
	quest.2977B0A071166015.quest_desc: ["The Copper Spool is used to make Alternator, Electric Motor or Tesla Coil"]
	quest.2981BA6FC0E8510A.quest_desc: ["&fMaylene, the Fighting-type Gym Leader of Veilstone City, is one of the official Sinnoh Gym World Tour battles. Defeat this leader, claim the matching badge, and continue your regional progression."]
	quest.2981BA6FC0E8510A.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 71"
	quest.2981BA6FC0E8510A.title: "Maylene"
	quest.298EBEB0D5346BDD.quest_desc: ["Now that you have a fossil, it's time to analyze it! The Monitor will help identify the species hidden within the ancient remains."]
	quest.298EBEB0D5346BDD.quest_subtitle: "What secrets does this fossil hold?"
	quest.298EBEB0D5346BDD.title: "Analyzing the Fossil"
	quest.2A6205E787F7931A.quest_desc: [
		"A Display Link is used to get information from a block and send it to blocks that can display it. "
		""
		"Display links have a range of 64 blocks by default"
	]
	quest.2A6A9041FE0C4888.quest_desc: ["Iron is the lifeblood of minecraft. If you need it, it probably uses iron. "]
	quest.2AA9784F0526D00D.quest_desc: ["The wither is a ferocious enemy. Summon him and defeat him to gain the powerfull nether star core that animates the skulls and sand."]
	quest.2AA9784F0526D00D.title: "Withering Heights"
	quest.2AADB51A9C011561.quest_desc: ["Nice, you got a full team!"]
	quest.2AADB51A9C011561.quest_subtitle: "A full Team!"
	quest.2AB27C463CE0C9F0.quest_desc: ["&fGordie, the Rock-type Gym Leader of Circhester, is one of the official Galar Gym World Tour battles. Defeat this leader, claim the matching badge, and continue your regional progression."]
	quest.2AB27C463CE0C9F0.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 100"
	quest.2AB27C463CE0C9F0.title: "Gordie"
	quest.2AB2FB362B403460.title: "Dusk Ball 2013 9"
	quest.2AC137852DA4C38E.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 55"
	quest.2AEA67F8C1A3A023.quest_desc: [
		"&bJEI&r (&dJust Enough Items&r) is one of the &emost important tools&r in this modpack."
		""
		"Many quests will require you to &esearch recipes&r, understand &bcrafting chains&r, or find how an item is used."
		""
		"&6How to use JEI:&r"
		""
		"• &eLeft click&r an item to see its &acrafting recipe&r  "
		"• &eRight click&r an item to see &bhow it is used&r  "
		"• Use the &aSearch Bar&r to quickly find items or machines  "
		""
		"&l&aTip:&r  "
		"If a quest asks you to craft something and you don't know how, always check &eJEI&r first."
		""
		"Most of the &banswers&r about crafting and progression can be found there."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&cImportant:&r  "
		"Some recipes may change depending on the modpack progression, so always verify them in &dJEI&r."
		""
		"If you still need help, you can ask other players on the &9Discord&r server or search &eonline&r."
		""
		"&7Don't worry if things feel confusing at first. With &eJEI&r, you'll quickly understand how everything connects together."
	]
	quest.2AEA67F8C1A3A023.quest_subtitle: "&bThe most important tool in your adventure"
	quest.2AEA67F8C1A3A023.title: "&eJEI Guide"
	quest.2B04C39F8061A391.quest_desc: [
		"Welcome to Our Story."
		""
		"Do you like exploring and discovering new lands? You also like to make automated machines to have unlimited resources? You'll find something for you in this modpack."
		""
		"Thanks to the future quests that will be set up, you will be able to write your story through exploration, technology, magic and many other mods."
		""
		"We wish you a good game!"
	]
	quest.2B04C39F8061A391.title: "Welcome"
	quest.2B9037536F9B9CA0.quest_desc: ["🔥 Flint’s burning spirit and flashy style keep the Elite Four energized. He's childhood friends with Champion Volkner!"]
	quest.2B9037536F9B9CA0.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 61"
	quest.2BDBD4D89FCDDF52.title: "&fA Wild &dEternatus &fAppeared!"
	quest.2BF9EDF75BFFAB84.title: "Dream Ball 2013 9"
	quest.2C0AFACD14F7ED1C.quest_desc: ["Some Pokémon from Galar display distinct regional forms. Even outside their original region, these genetic traits persist. By capturing 50 of them, you’ll be able to study this fascinating continuity."]
	quest.2C0AFACD14F7ED1C.title: "Obtain 50 different Pokémon from Generation 8's Pokédex"
	quest.2C2A6B2C351DBE24.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 70"
	quest.2C2A6B2C351DBE24.title: "Cheren"
	quest.2C52FC379CE4C378.quest_desc: [
		"By default, each Item Vault block has a storage space of 20 stacks"
		""
		"Item Vaults will connect with other Item Vaults. 1 tall vaults can be up to 3 blocks long, 2x2 tall item vaults can be 6 blocks long, and 3x3 tall vaults can be 9 blocks long, resulting in a maximum storage space of 1620 stacks in one Item Vault multiblock."
	]
	quest.2C8290C44890E0B5.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.2C8290C44890E0B5.quest_subtitle: "Diving Gear is used with Copper Backtank for underwater mobility."
	quest.2C8290C44890E0B5.title: "Craft &6Diving Kit"
	quest.2C8DC970C9A96B94.title: "&fA Wild &5Genesect &fAppeared!"
	quest.2CAC4F7593B6F49E.title: "&fA Wild &bPhione &fAppeared!"
	quest.2CDFB51DDFAFEFA0.title: "Capture the legendary &5Hoopa"
	quest.2D03D5F5B823323A.title: "Net Ball 2013 9"
	quest.2D87505812794E74.quest_desc: ["&eFilters&r allow you to control which items are allowed to enter a specific inventory."]
	quest.2DB16E3FA1CA6062.quest_desc: ["&fA Rich Mulch increases the yield of the harvest of the Berry Tree that it is used on for 3 harvests"]
	quest.2DD27C4A0CB56BF1.quest_desc: ["Did you know you could make an automated shop with this mod? Go ahead and try setting up a vending machine"]
	quest.2DD27C4A0CB56BF1.quest_subtitle: "Player Shop"
	quest.2DEADACEBE389031.quest_desc: ["You’ve captured the essence of Unova. This is not just a modern region: it’s a complex mosaic, reflecting both the evolution of our society and that of its Pokémon."]
	quest.2DEADACEBE389031.title: "Obtain 156 different Pokémon from Generation 5's Pokédex"
	quest.2E07C595CCE93B79.quest_desc: ["Pokémon from Sinnoh often carry an ancestral aura. Even the most common ones seem linked to a bygone era. Start your observation with 20 of them. Analyze their behaviors, their forms... You might uncover a silent wisdom."]
	quest.2E07C595CCE93B79.title: "Obtain 20 different Pokémon from Generation 4's Pokédex"
	quest.2E54CF3858793E28.quest_desc: ["Catch the favorite Pokemon of the person who made these quests. Thanks everyone who downloaded this and enjoyed it!"]
	quest.2E54CF3858793E28.title: "Team Clarissa"
	quest.2E54E17AB69B8D5C.title: "Vegitarian?"
	quest.2E666C9D6BCB320E.quest_desc: ["You’ve now gathered enough data to study the typical evolutionary lines of Kanto. These often involve three clearly distinct stages. Observe their evolution, abilities, and how they interact with their environment."]
	quest.2E666C9D6BCB320E.title: "Obtain 100 different Pokémon from Generation 1's Pokédex"
	quest.2E6D783CB515DC00.title: "&fA Wild &eThundurus &fAppeared!"
	quest.2E82B8B267E28E1B.quest_desc: [
		"&fGive your &bslot 1 Pokémon&f a toy-like appearance by setting its size to &cMini (0.3)&f.  "
		"&c⚠ Reminder: Only affects the first Pokémon in your party (slot 1). Double-check before using!  "
		""
		"&f💰 Cost: &e25 Realm Coins  "
	]
	quest.2E82B8B267E28E1B.quest_subtitle: "&eShrink your Pokémon to the smallest scale"
	quest.2E82B8B267E28E1B.title: "&6Mini Size"
	quest.2E9F87E12C2688A5.quest_desc: [
		"The Brass Tunnel is a machine that can only be placed on Mechanical Belts. It can sort items that pass through."
		""
		"You can put a filter on this funnel, and it can extract a stack at a time !"
	]
	quest.2E9F87E12C2688A5.title: "Brass Tunnel"
	quest.2EB779BBD6F1BECF.quest_desc: ["&fCeladon City’s calm Grass-type leader hides dangerous control behind graceful manners. Cut through the petals and do not let the fight take root."]
	quest.2EB779BBD6F1BECF.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 25"
	quest.2EB779BBD6F1BECF.title: "Erika"
	quest.2EF042A8083928B4.title: "Moon Ball 2013 9"
	quest.2EF6003F9EC0467E.title: "Maybe just a taste"
	quest.2EFA38D9491535EA.quest_subtitle: "&eDisplay links&r can read blocks and output information to linked displays. Perfect for reading inventories etc."
	quest.2EFA38D9491535EA.title: "Craft &6Display Link"
	quest.2F2ADEC6F4BCE766.quest_desc: ["With a level 4 beacon, so long as your storage is chunkloaded, you can access your storage from anywhere using this wireless terminal. "]
	quest.2F2ADEC6F4BCE766.quest_subtitle: "Level 4 Beacon"
	quest.2F5433F8FA15F7F6.quest_desc: ["Iron chests is a mod that allows you to make larger chests that take up the same ammount of space. Its also a good way to make use of the billions of copper you probably have"]
	quest.2F5433F8FA15F7F6.quest_subtitle: "Useful Copper!"
	quest.2FEAB5AF61EBCCEE.quest_desc: ["&fIn Cobblemon, the damage of a specific type is boosted by three main families of items:&r &6Plates&r (often associated with &7Iron&r or &8Obsidian&r), &bAugments&r (generally linked to &dAmethyst&r or &bCrystals&r), and the &aTraditional Type Boosting Items&r (like &eMagnet&r for &eElectric&r &7or&r &8Charcoal&r for &4Fire&r), all of which typically grant the same &c+20% damage boost&r to their corresponding type."]
	quest.2FEAB5AF61EBCCEE.title: "&eCobblemon Held Items"
	quest.30090644644B4142.quest_desc: ["The Overworld is a vast, diverse land where every biome holds new surprises. From lush forests to towering mountains and endless oceans, this is where your journey begins. Explore, catch Pokémon, gather resources, and uncover the hidden secrets of this vibrant, living world."]
	quest.30090644644B4142.quest_subtitle: "The Overworld: The Heart of the Adventure"
	quest.301F1696722B5175.quest_desc: ["&fFuchsia City’s Poison-type ninja relies on traps, pressure, and dirty tempo. Keep your footing or his tactics will wear your team down."]
	quest.301F1696722B5175.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 25"
	quest.301F1696722B5175.title: "Koga"
	quest.303A47753A92FCED.quest_desc: ["When thrown, this ball will fly further, allowing you to try to capture pokemon at a further distance, including pokemon mid air or otherwise out of reach"]
	quest.3044817E237CB362.quest_desc: ["The legends of Johto speak of Pokémon linked to rebirth, the cycle of life. Ho-Oh, Suicune, and many more… But even without encountering these mythical figures, you can still feel their influence. Continue your research with 60 captures. This knowledge will guide you on paths older than memory."]
	quest.3044817E237CB362.title: "Obtain 60 different Pokémon from Generation 2's Pokédex"
	quest.3054F81E485394B8.quest_desc: ["Some Pokémon from Paldea defy any known biological logic. They are fascinating anomalies. Their presence in this world remains a mystery… and a true scientific treasure."]
	quest.3054F81E485394B8.title: "Obtain 100 different Pokémon from Generation 9's Pokédex"
	quest.30797188C37D1D48.quest_desc: [
		"The tutorial is now &afinished&r! "
		""
		"New quests will appear in the menu on the left, sorted by category. Some will only appear in secret *shh*."
		""
		"Feel free to join our &bDiscord &rfor any other questions you may have: https://discord.gg/kb8NSTF45n"
	]
	quest.30797188C37D1D48.quest_subtitle: "Read my description!"
	quest.3091426850216D82.quest_subtitle: "&eUsed to connect to other &2Cogs &rand &2Large Cogwheels&r. Needed early on to power specific machines like the &9Mechanical Mixer &ror &9Millstone&r."
	quest.3091426850216D82.title: "Craft &cCogwheels"
	quest.30C269E0695A704D.quest_desc: ["&fViridian City’s final Kanto leader fights with ruthless Ground-type power and boss-level control. Defeating him marks the end of your first regional trial."]
	quest.30C269E0695A704D.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 28"
	quest.30C269E0695A704D.title: "Giovanni"
	quest.310DF134407136A4.quest_desc: ["If you really cant get a specific type of dye, this will allow you to trade for it at a loss"]
	quest.310FDF97D1E0681F.quest_desc: ["The Nature Compass is an essential tool for exploring and finding specific biomes in the world. It allows you to locate any biome you desire and navigate towards it with ease.\\n\\nTo use the Nature Compass:\\n1. Craft or find a Nature Compass.\\n2. Right-click to open the Nature Compass interface.\\n3. Select the biome you wish to find from the list.\\n4. The compass will point towards the selected biome and guide you in the right direction.\\n\\nNote: The compass only works when you have already discovered the biome at least once. Happy exploring!"]
	quest.310FDF97D1E0681F.quest_subtitle: "&eNature Compass Explanation"
	quest.31170C0F6A7AA37D.quest_subtitle: "&bForest, Mushroom, Spooky, Swamp"
	quest.3120A1970CA00E14.quest_subtitle: "Are You Ready? You Only Get 1 Shot."
	quest.3120A1970CA00E14.title: "Catch all 3 Legendaries"
	quest.3178302C98DE92A8.title: "Catch Cute Pokemon"
	quest.318320E94E7DCD64.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 69"
	quest.318320E94E7DCD64.title: "Octo"
	quest.318593DEE275F999.quest_desc: ["A Wrench can be used to give the tunnel windows. The Tunnel does not stop items on the belt from being processed by an Encased Fan, but does stop the airflow from going beyond the belt. Andesite Tunnels can also be used to separate single items from passing stacks to side outputs."]
	quest.318593DEE275F999.title: "Craft &bAndesite Tunnels"
	quest.31E318411D2C06D5.title: "&fA Wild &9Kyogre &fAppeared!"
	quest.31E69CA962A58692.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.31E69CA962A58692.quest_subtitle: "Smart Fluid Pipes can be used to allow only a certain liquid to pass through them. This can be set by placing a bucket or bottle of the liquid in the Filter slot on the pipe. A List Filter with Respect Data on may be required for the Smart Pipe to distinguish between certain liquids, such as Potions."
	quest.31E69CA962A58692.title: "Craft &6Smart Fluid Pipe"
	quest.32035F371C7A066F.quest_desc: ["Behind Kalos’ refined aesthetic lies a complex lineage. Each species has a rich, sometimes noble, history."]
	quest.32035F371C7A066F.title: "Obtain 50 different Pokémon from Generation 6's Pokédex"
	quest.320C3ECD5EEDCEF2.title: "&fA Wild &cGalarian Moltres &fAppeared!"
	quest.320FD873A45EB92F.quest_desc: ["Cilan is a Pokémon Connoisseur who believes that battles are like finely prepared dishes — a balance of flavor and strategy. As one of the Striaton Triplets, he tests your understanding of Pokémon types and taste"]
	quest.320FD873A45EB92F.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 25"
	quest.320FD873A45EB92F.title: "Cilan"
	quest.322DD3E3032D83FA.quest_desc: [
		"&6&l🏆 Kalos Trainer Progression — League Challenge"
		""
		"&fTake on Kalos’s prestigious Elite Four and Champion Diantha in this high-stakes League arc!"
		""
		"&b⏩ &nClick bellow to view the full trainer path:&r &7"
		"{\"text\":\"Kalos League Graph Link\",\"italic\":true,\"clickEvent\":{\"action\":\"open_url\",\"value\":\"https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/svg/~1U06Lb45Fwp0GXE_-5Kiv8oX7L5b8S0C92JWYeKszZKqSRx0tLF34VtzEOsX5YnIEzep7twoZN2R1A7thrP5OQWcygwtK4T-LEF44inlqdE2MiEu9hYnwJw6ccRBE42IXI2pl7QLnewMsefXKQbpeC6AR0mCD1k0ebdS4hbveAV1FOOoylcBF4OuZcN7zQDso2PGIdAiAbqqTkG-ck3QGbU_ffxHOS2UE0tgjuPWZPjHzZw4LeP0PFDk-dpjidceA9hFjNRssJaYjE4XXgNocssmyk0-2-Lnzgd9Sk0DFAr6BIjzk4XUdbLPvcOzSZ5SFBJJSqsllSdV8XgnfA9QnWOQxqkgd_asluRgK-hAeN63aK6NIiumnFpiR69v2CpphqcBRvN4z6uT1BCu04nnKViyWdmUouZu-9qSLUxCDsPEcf9Y8AUoGR4D6PKh6sZL98hU7KBwqAJaj-hU3A1j17PmKdFWJFGvnY_vN_pVaz2lATAOVAC-bBlE7ady0_m4D7dZp\"}}"
		""
		"&9🔄 Want to switch to the Kalos League path?  "
