	quest.5BFCDE258C810A82.title: "Capture the legendary &cMoltres"
	quest.5C4656243EB3EB53.quest_desc: ["Minecart Coupling is used to make minecart or minecart contraption trains. "]
	quest.5C95FF3125CA51B0.quest_subtitle: "A key ingredient for many of the more complicated blocks in &6Create&r. You'll definitely want to automate production of these at some stage."
	quest.5C95FF3125CA51B0.title: "Obtain Brass"
	quest.5CD7917FA2A57B85.title: "Capture the legendary &5Spectrier"
	quest.5CE0BFE0D1AA9D2B.quest_desc: ["Fossils are ancient Pokémon remains buried deep within the world. Use a brush on Suspicious Sand or Suspicious Gravel in fossil structures to uncover them!"]
	quest.5CE0BFE0D1AA9D2B.quest_subtitle: "Uncover the past hidden in sand and gravel!"
	quest.5CE0BFE0D1AA9D2B.title: "Buried Secrets"
	quest.5D09328C1ABE02B6.quest_desc: ["The Portable Storage Interface is a block that allows Item Transporters to directly interact with Contraption inventories. "]
	quest.5D14EE24B68A0B02.title: "&fA Wild &bDialga &fAppeared!"
	quest.5D163FA97D88AC77.quest_desc: ["The Nature Compass is an essential tool for exploring and finding specific biomes in the world. It allows you to locate any biome you desire and navigate towards it with ease.\\n\\nTo use the Nature Compass:\\n1. Craft or find a Nature Compass.\\n2. Right-click to open the Nature Compass interface.\\n3. Select the biome you wish to find from the list.\\n4. The compass will point towards the selected biome and guide you in the right direction.\\n\\nNote: The compass only works when you have already discovered the biome at least once. Happy exploring!"]
	quest.5D163FA97D88AC77.quest_subtitle: "&eNature Compass Explanation"
	quest.5D1BA4DC2B47A924.quest_desc: ["&fA Loamy Mulch makes the Berry Tree act like it's in a Plains biome for an infinite duration."]
	quest.5D2605C816B31F0D.title: "Storage Connectors"
	quest.5D39ABA701DF48B6.quest_desc: [
		"- Schematic And Quill:"
		"Used to save blueprints of a structure."
		""
		"- Empty Schematic:"
		"Used as a recipe ingredient and for writing at the Schematic Table."
	]
	quest.5D39ABA701DF48B6.quest_subtitle: "Click"
	quest.5D5EF7C254842676.quest_desc: ["The &6Gems&f are &bconsumable items&f that can be &e[held by a Pokémon]&f, and have the effect of &asignificantly boosting the power&f of the &cthe first move&f of the &dcorresponding type&f used by the holder."]
	quest.5DA5BDBEF3085B4B.quest_desc: ["The islands of Alola are famous for their endemic species, different forms of species found elsewhere. Some Pokémon have even developed special abilities in response to the islands’ unique ecosystem. By capturing 30 Pokémon, you'll better understand these fascinating adaptations."]
	quest.5DA5BDBEF3085B4B.title: "Obtain 30 different Pokémon from Generation 7's Pokédex"
	quest.5DABA1DA693D4222.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 75"
	quest.5DABA1DA693D4222.title: "Inky"
	quest.5DE6BAC0314B40DB.title: "Capture the legendary &6Urshifu"
	quest.5E216C5F27D90883.quest_subtitle: "If the &dContent Observer&r is placed with the front facing a container, Mechanical Belt, Funnel or Fluid Pipe, it will emit a &cRedstone signal&r when an item is detected inside. If a filter is applied to the Content Observer, it will only emit a redstone signal when the item in the filter is detected."
	quest.5E216C5F27D90883.title: "Craft a &6Content Observer"
	quest.5E340215D732510A.quest_desc: ["Warning: Ancient Heavy balls, Leaden balls, and Gigaton Balls have no effect right now. "]
	quest.5E491777A8F21417.title: "Capture the legendary &5Wo-Chien"
	quest.5E77F9BB5DB28086.title: "Capture the legendary &5Ting-Lu"
	quest.5E9CE2534C4886CA.title: "&fA Wild &bGalarian Articuno &fAppeared!"
	quest.5EA80D9C3C190DA2.quest_desc: ["In the Blast Furnace you need to put Ironwood to obtain Steel."]
	quest.5EBD3E66FA49BF12.title: "Capture the legendary &aZarude"
	quest.5EC07AF7256E43AD.quest_subtitle: "&bDesert, Floral, Magical, Savanna, Spooky"
	quest.5EC1446EA85C2097.quest_desc: ["Surely rare pokemon must spawn within the beautiful pink trees of this place"]
	quest.5EC1446EA85C2097.quest_subtitle: "An Ocean of Pink"
	quest.5EDE08B527D6FAD9.title: "&fA Wild &cLatias &fAppeared!"
	quest.5F0D6FB5448862E1.quest_desc: [
		"The Encased Fan is a mechanical component that can create air streams and generate power."
		"Its air streams are used for moving entities or for Bulk Washing, Bulk Blasting, and Bulk Smoking."
	]
	quest.5F1C85E1E1A57DF9.quest_subtitle: "&bRecommended: ~Lv 13"
	quest.5F1C85E1E1A57DF9.title: "Bianca"
	quest.5F31490CB71F1B9E.quest_desc: ["The Toolbox can hold up to 256 items per slot and up to 8 different types of items"]
	quest.5F3C22D846BA566C.quest_desc: ["Can store different items that are not stackable, as long as they belong to the same category."]
	quest.5F96FB085395512D.quest_desc: ["The &6Gems&f are &bconsumable items&f that can be &e[held by a Pokémon]&f, and have the effect of &asignificantly boosting the power&f of the &cthe first move&f of the &dcorresponding type&f used by the holder."]
	quest.5FB0DE42C30B6088.quest_desc: ["Works like an &eInventory Cable&r but its appearance can be changed using the &ePaint Kit&r."]
	quest.5FBDFE01BAFC4141.quest_subtitle: "&bJungle, Temperate, Lush"
	quest.60080CCE5A743510.quest_desc: ["&fMarlon, the Water-type Gym Leader of Humilau City, is one of the official Unova Gym World Tour battles. Defeat this leader, claim the matching badge, and continue your regional progression."]
	quest.60080CCE5A743510.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 89"
	quest.60080CCE5A743510.title: "Marlon"
	quest.60229AA46322C9C7.quest_desc: ["The Pokémon of Alola are deeply tied to their environment. Many display more peaceful behaviors, in harmony with nature. As you capture more, you'll discover unique habits related to their natural habitats like beaches or lush forests."]
	quest.60229AA46322C9C7.title: "Obtain 45 different Pokémon from Generation 7's Pokédex"
	quest.60308EA5FAA85DD8.quest_desc: ["&fFlannery, the Fire-type Gym Leader of Lavaridge Town, is one of the official Hoenn Gym World Tour battles. Defeat this leader, claim the matching badge, and continue your regional progression."]
	quest.60308EA5FAA85DD8.quest_subtitle: "&bUnlocked Level Cap: Lv 54"
	quest.60308EA5FAA85DD8.title: "Flannery"
	quest.603F1D71DAAA35F9.quest_subtitle: "&bJungle, Swamp"
	quest.605D662596B4B8EE.quest_desc: ["The region of Hoenn has one of the highest biodiversity rates. As you reach 80 captures, don't hesitate to explore extreme environments: volcanic caves, remote beaches, dense canopies… Every capture is another piece of the ecological puzzle."]
	quest.605D662596B4B8EE.title: "Obtain 80 different Pokémon from Generation 3's Pokédex"
	quest.608F2716B3429CCD.quest_desc: ["Mechanical Pump is used to extract fluid from a fluid pipe or a fluid tank."]
	quest.60DFC7FBE95E6BE5.quest_desc: ["Smart Chutes behave similarly to Brass Funnels. They can be filtered to only allow certain items through, and be stopped with a redstone signal. Unlike funnels, they can insert and extract at the same time, but can only function vertically."]
